<h1>
Sword</h1>

<h2>
Applies to</h2>
Compiling the sword binaries and development CVS files.
<h2>
Procedure for compiling sword for use with bibletime:</h2>
Open the file
<br>&nbsp;
<blockquote>~/sword/Makefile.cvs</blockquote>

<p><br>find the lines for <b>shared library</b> and <b>VCL library</b>,
and change to yes as shown
<br>below:
<br>&nbsp;
<blockquote>##### Customizable stuff. Set it how you like it #####
<p># compiler
<p>CROSS_COMPILE =
<br>CC&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; = gcc
<br>need_local_regex := no
<br>&nbsp;
<p># shared library- set to yes if you would like to build
<p>buildshare := yes
<br>&nbsp;
<p># VCL library- set to yes if you would like to build
<p>buildvcl := no
<br>&nbsp;
<p># Debugging options etc...
<p>debug&nbsp;&nbsp; := no
<br>profile := no
<br>&nbsp;
<p># endian, etc. support for other hardware
<p>system := intel
<br>#system := sparc
<br>#system := macosx
<br>#system := arm
<p>## MAC OSX Support works but possible bug exists in /usr/include/sys/dirent.h
<br>## on the current version (B) of OSX.&nbsp; You will need to add this
line right after the #ifdef of DIRENT
<br>#include &lt;sys/types.h>
<br>&nbsp;
<p># zLib support
<p>zlib := yes
<br>&nbsp;
<p># paths
<p>instdir&nbsp;&nbsp; := /usr
<p>bindir&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; := ${instdir}/bin
<br>libdir&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; := ${instdir}/lib
<br>hdir&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; := ${instdir}/include/sword
<br>docdir&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; := ${instdir}/doc/sword
<br>confdir&nbsp;&nbsp; := ${instdir}/share/sword
<br>&nbsp;
<br>&nbsp;
<p>#------------------------------------------------------------------------------#
<br># You shouldn't need to change anything below here.
<br>&nbsp;</blockquote>
The remainder of the user customization files can be set to your preference.
<p>Now to compile sword do
<br>&nbsp;
<blockquote>cd ~/sword
<br>./configure
<br>make
<br>su
<br>make install</blockquote>

<p><br>Sword is now prepaired for use with bibletime.
<h1>
Installmgr</h1>

<h2>
Applies to</h2>
Compiling theinstallmgr program included with sword binaries and development
CVS files.
<h2>
Procedure for compiling Installmgr for use with bibletime:</h2>
If you would use installmgr to load sword modules, make sure that the gtk
libraries are installed.
<br>Now open a new terminal and do
<br>&nbsp;
<blockquote>cd ~/sword/apps/X11/InstallMgr
<br>./configure
<br>make
<br>su
<br>make install</blockquote>

<p><br>installmgr can now be launched by typing as superuser or root
<br>&nbsp;
<blockquote>/usr/local/bin/installmgr</blockquote>

<p><br>If the above instructions do not work on your system, please read
the <b>INSTALL</b>
<br>files.
<p>Additional information is also contained in the bibletime DOC file "Sword
module installation program (installmgr)"</b>
<br>&nbsp;
<br>&nbsp;
<br>&nbsp;
